The paper is about building and analyzing artificial neural network architectures using an energy-based approach. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The methodology is based on unsupervised learning, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also present experimental results related to computer vision (cs.CV) and systems and control (cs.SY).
